\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 62. A. glaberrima} (Rech. fil.) W. Greuter,{\i  op. cit.} 148 (1968) ({\i Ammanthus glaberrimus} Rech. fil.). Glabrous or sparsely hairy  annual. Stems 2-30 cm, flexuous. Leaves pinnatisect to 3-fid or entire, more or less petiolate, fleshy; segments distant, ovate- cuneate, more or less deeply divided or entire; lobes subobtuse to acute. Capitula up to 10 mm in diameter. Involucre appressed- hairy; bracts obtuse, the outer ovate to oblong, the inner broadly  elliptical, with wide hyaline margin. Ligules c. 2 mm, broadly elliptical, pink. Receptacle shortly conical, acute; scales lanceolate-cuneate to narrowly linear, acute, hyaline, rather shorter than florets, glabrous, caducous. Achenes 1-1·25 mm (excluding corona) and nearly as wide as long, obsoletely ribbed, cylindrical- turbinate; corona up to 0·5 mm on the adaxial side, rather shorter to almost absent on abaxial side, erose-lacerate, hyaline.{\i  Calcareous rocks. • N.W. Kriti} ({\i island of Gramvousa}). Cr.
