\pard\f0\fs28 Perennial herbs. Leaves entire to 3-pinnatifid, alternate. Capitula usually small, pedunculate, rarely shortly so. Involucral bracts in few rows, the outer somewhat shorter than the inner, with a scarious margin. Receptacle convex or conical; scales present. Outer florets ligulate, female, the ligules more or less 3-dentate, patent or rarely short and erect. Inner florets hermaphrodite, 5-lobed, white, yellow or pink; corolla-tube compressed. Achenes compressed, oblong or obovate; pappus absent.
